cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.AL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with algorithms for building and maintaining DFS trees in graphs, which is a fundamental data structure in graph theory. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GR). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis (cs.DM) and experimental evaluation (cs.NE) of the algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the design and analysis of algorithms (cs.AL) for incremental DFS.
